column209: Thanks for allowing me to participate! Have a great day!
I don’t buy products based on company values. I don’t take into consideration what kind of company it is. Why does it matter?
Big companies are not human and we can't expect them to behave like human beings.
I definitely wouldn't purchase clothing from this company.
Coca-Cola needs to stop putting formaldehyde in their soda
Companies usually advertise falsely, but just enough so they don't get caught. The majority of the public believes what they see in ads.
Nobody ever remembers the good.  They'll remember the bad.
Thank you for the survey opportunity.
Companies will never have true values as long as next quarter's shareholder profit if the main priority. Also, Coca-Cola murders union members and Nike relies on slave labor.
Corporate America has ceded its soul to greed. Our nation is so much the worse because of that.
I'd like to think big companies have some form of a moral compass. Some do, however, there are some like Facebook are only out for profit and i really don't care about anyone.
"oca-Cola is about community-driven fun, Patagonia is about connecting with nature, and Nike is about bringing out the best version of you." ...Lmao

Wanted to say that I just graduated from community college, wasn't sure if that fell under the technical/vocational school option, so I just put "some college". Everything went smoothly otherwise, thank you!

Yeah, I get what you were driving at, but the latter sets of questions about big companies were all over the place with a lot of vague metrics. They could have been expressed more precisely and narrowly - sort of how the above passage debriefed the study's mission.
It seemed like the purpose was to ascribe psychopathic qualities to large companies.
The study concerned how consumers perceive the ethics of ;large corporations.
No matter what the companies say about their "values" the goal of any company is to make money for its owners.
Good luck to you with your research.
I question where some of these values are true or if they are just to drive profits.
In my view, the larger the company the greater the impulse to make money, and the more powerful the people entrusted to steer toward that end. The changes you describe seem to be all marketing.
Thank you for the study and money. Stay safe!

I believe there are alot of good companies out there but I also believe many are in it to just make a profit at the expense of the consumer. It is well and good when companies make improvements but it should be across the entire company not just certain departments.
If they were using underpaid workers for some of the work, that was an indication of who they were from the beginning
